## Agent conventions

This repo adopts the [agent-stack](https://github.com/<your-org>/agent-stack)
framework. The framework's `core/` docs (in this repo at
`vendor/agent-stack/core/`, or installed via the init script
under `docs/agents/`) carry the stack-agnostic rules. This
file adds the project-specific guidance that sits alongside
those rules.

## Commit and branch policy

See `docs/agents/commit-and-branch.md` (or the bundled copy
at `vendor/agent-stack/core/commit-and-branch.md`).

## Bugs

See `docs/agents/bug-patterns.md` for the catalog and
`docs/agents/issue-tracker.md` (or `issues/bug-template.md`
in the framework) for the bug protocol.

## Features

See `docs/agents/feature-protocol.md` for the slice
discipline and `docs/agents/issue-tracker.md` (or
`issues/feature-template.md` in the framework) for the
feature protocol.

## Domain vocabulary

See [CONTEXT.md](CONTEXT.md) for the project's glossary. Read
it end-to-end before writing any user-facing copy or
schema-touching code.

## CHANGELOG

Every user-visible change gets a bullet in [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md)
`[Unreleased]` under the right heading in the same commit
that lands the change.